1. install the following rpms for vnc: (if you have epl yum repository you can use "yum install vnc")
	tigervnc-server-1.0.90-0.17.20110314svn4359.el6.x86_64
	tigervnc-1.0.90-0.17.20110314svn4359.el6.x86_64
2. configure the file /etc/sysconfig/vncservers (create one if it is not created automatically)
3. stop and start vncserver service
